0. Note, if installing Percona, do *not* install MySQL

I. Download the MySQL APT repository
   A. APT repository is for Debian systems (of which Mint is an offshoot)
   B. Other repositories exist for other operating systems
   C. https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/repo/apt/

II. Install/run the download package by navigating to the containing folder and running:
   A. $ sudo dpkg -i mysql-apt-config 0.8.9-1_all.deb
  
III. Select the most appropriate Debian release (9)
   A. After install, run the command:
   B. $ sudo apt-get update
   
IV. To confirm installation:
   A. $ mysql -V
   
V. Alternatively, download either:
   A. Wither Percona Server for MySQL (Ubuntu 16.04 - Xenial Xerus)
   B. Mariadb

VI. For Percona:
   A. Download the appropriate .tar for the operating environment
   B. Run:
      1. $ tar xvf <filename>.tar
      2. TODO: (xvf) meaning?
      3. $ sudo dpkg -i *.deb

